Mobile service provider Infinix Zero 5 flagship is seemingly the must have smartphone in the market after its recent launch. Launched on November 14th, the Zero 5 Pro is a complete upgrade compared to the Zero 4 and Zero 4 Plus with special features like an Octa Core Helio P25 processor from Mediatek giving it a fluid performance. Display With a 5.98-inch touchscreen display with a resolution of 1080 pixels by 1920 pixels, a 12-megapixel primary camera on the rear and a 16-megapixel front shooter for selfies making it the company’s flagship going into 2018 and is a camera-centric device just like all the devices under the ‘Zero’ family. This is achieved given its dual setup of 12 MP wide-angle lens and 13 MP telephoto lens is a snappy shooter with lots of modes to tinker around with just to let get a good shot.   Global Head of Infinix, Benjamin Jiang said the device, the lates of Zero series hopes to bridge the gap between amateur & professional photography. With its innovative design, incredible dual camera, 2x Optical zoom and overall performance, the Infinix Zero 5 bridges the narrowing gap between smartphone and tablet. "The Zero series at large has been our flagship product globally by virtue of its innovative features and validates our R&D prowess with the Zero 5 smartphone is Infinix’s most high-end and technologically-advanced product to date."  The Infinix Zero 5 Pro is a dual SIM (GSM and GSM) smartphone that accepts Micro-SIM and Macro-SIM. Sensors on the phone include Proximity sensor, Accelerometer, Ambient light sensor and Gyroscope.  